JOHANNESBURG - The ANC Youth League says creating the position of another deputy secretary general, will help the party keep track on the implementation of its promises.The youth league reiterated its call for a Top 7 at its media briefing on Tuesday. The young lions also made clear its preferred candidate to lead the mother body, come December.They say former African Union Chairperson Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma fits the mould of a "committed leader ".The league's Njabulo Nzuza told eNCA on Wednesday morning, that the requirements they have set disqualified Cyril Ramaphosa as President Jacob Zuma's successor.Video courtesy of DStv channel 403.eNCA